### 3.3 Core Equations

**Fee Growth Conversion (to numeraire):**

```
$monopolisticFeeGrowth = sqrtPriceX96 Ă feeGrowthOutside0x128 + feeGrowthOutside1x128

$feeGrowthInside_pos = sqrtPriceX96 Ă feeGrowthInside0x128_pos + feeGrowthInside1x128_pos
```

**Fee Compression Ratio:**

```
fee_ratio_i = $monopolisticFeeGrowth / $feeGrowthInside_pos

log_fee_ratio_i = ln(fee_ratio_i)
```

**Cross-Sectional Variance:**

```
variance_t = (1/N) Ă ÎŁ^N (log_fee_ratio_i - mean_t)Â˛

where: mean_t = (1/N) Ă ÎŁ^N log_fee_ratio_i
```

**Price of Anarchy:**

```
P_{#LP_t} = Ď^monopolistic_t / Ď^competitive_t

where:
Ď^monopolistic_t = mean(feeGrowth for JIT positions at t)
Ď^competitive_t = mean(feeGrowth for passive positions at t)
```

**Core Claim (to validate):**

```
H0: ln(variance_t) = ln(P_{#LP_t}) + Îľ_t

Test: Regress ln(variance_t) on ln(P_{#LP_t})
Expected: coefficient â 1, intercept â 0, RÂ˛ > 0.5
```

**Baseline Regression (determinants):**

```
log_fee_ratio_i = Îą + Î˛Âˇ1_{retail(i)} + ÎłâÂˇlog(tick_range_i) 
                + ÎłâÂˇlog(size_i) + ÎłâÂˇmoneyness_i + ÎłâÂˇvolatility_t + Î´_t + Îľ_i

Interpretation:
Î˛ > 0: Retail suffers more fee compression
Îłâ: Effect of tick range width
Îłâ: Effect of position size
Îłâ: Effect of moneyness (ITM/OTM)
Îłâ: Effect of market volatility
```

**Optimal Liquidity (from theory):**

```
liquidity*(tickSpread) = ((#Positions - 1) / #Positions) Ă 
    (feeGrowth_informed / feeGrowth_uninformed - hedging_cost)

Hypothesis: Optimal liquidity decreases with #LPs (competition effect)
```

**FCS Payoff (derivative specification):**

```
Linear: Î ^FCS = Notional Ă (realized_variance - strike_variance)

Log: Î ^FCS = Notional Ă (ln(realized_variance) - ln(strike_variance))

Digital: Î ^FCS = Notional Ă 1_{realized_variance > strike_variance}
